description: From the pages of DC's smash hit VILLAINS UNITED comes the 6-issue tale of a mysterious team of misfits that walks the line between good and evil, taking on the dirtiest, craziest tasks in the DCU! Their first mission — to rescue one of their own from a North Korean prison before he's executed — leads them to the realization that someone is trying to have them all killed. But who has it in for them?
name: Six Degrees of Devastation

volume.name: Secret Six: Six Degrees of Devastation

description: An indescribably powerful cosmic being gathers nine of Marvel’s most mismatched super beings for purposes beyond their comprehension. Can Spider-Man, Gravity, Venom, Henry Pym, the Wasp, Medusa, Kraven, Firebird and the Hood keep from killing each other until they must face the dangers of their destination, the deadly artificial planet known as Battleworld?

This issue features an exclusive look at the upcoming Power Core Combiners line, including a Q&A with our friends on the Transformers Team at Hasbro who are responsible for this great new line. Fans will also get to read the official back story for the Combiners and learn the secrets of Power Core Combination!

Also this issue, the Coming Storm Part 2! In addition to seeing the Elite Guard team featuring Metalhawk and Dion in action, ANOTHER group of Autobots will join the Elite Guard ranks. These Autobots are fresh out of the Academy and ready to put an end to the war! Who are these new Elite Guard members? Let's just say everything you thought you knew about this team is about to change!

Contents

  • On the cover: Stock photography of Power Core Combiners figures.
  • Brian's Bytes and Bolts, From the Editor's Desk (inside cover)
  • "Derrick Wyatt! - A TCC Interview" (p. 3) - Interview with Derrick Wyatt
  • "HASBRO INTERVIEW!" (pp. 4-5) - Interview with Hasbro about Power Core Combiners, including a sidebar that explains their in-fiction backstory.
  • Profile: Magnum (p. 6)
  • Profile: Over-Run (p. 7)
  • "Transformers: 2010 - part 2" by Jim Sorenson (p. 8) - Information and pictures about Trypticon.
  • "THE MAKING OF THE BOTCON EXCLUSIVES" (p. 9) - A quick look at one figure from each of the previous BotCon figure sets.
  • "The Coming Storm: Part 2" - comic story (pp. 10-15)
  • Around Cybertron (Wings of Honor version), "Featured Fan Art!" with "Aureus" by Julian "Rodimus Zero," Snowblind's profile (back cover)
